0country%20or%20target.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20%26quot%3Binformed%20the%20countries%20concerned%20in%20advance%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20a%20separate%20Xinhua%20report%2C%20which%20did%20not%20clarify%20the%20path%20of%20the%20missile%20or%20where%20exactly%20in%20the%20%26quot%3Bhigh%20seas%20of%20the%20Pacific%20Ocean%26quot%3B%20it%20fell.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20launch%20%26quot%3Beffectively%20tested%20the%20performance%20of%20weapons%20and%20equipment%20and%20the%20training%20level%20of%20the%20troops%2C%20and%20achieved%20the%20expected%20goal%2C%26quot%3B%20Xinhua%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20PLA%20Rocket%20Force%2C%20which%20oversees%20the%20country's%20conventional%20and%20nuclear%20missiles%2C%20has%20been%20tasked%20with%20modernising%20China's%20nuclear%20forces%20to%20deter%20developments%20such%20as%20improved%20U.S.%20missile%20defences%2C%20better%20surveillance%20capabilities%2C%20and%20strengthened%20alliances.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20analysts%2C%20however%2C%20argue%20the%20speed%20of%20China's%20nuclear%20build-up%20goes%20beyond%20a%20credible%20minimum%20deterrence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeijing%20says%20it%20adheres%20to%20a%20%26quot%3Bno%20first%20use%26quot%3B%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chinese%20military%20has%20emphasised%20that%20the%20Central%20Military%20Commission%2C%20headed%20by%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%2C%20is%20the%20only%20nuclear%20command%20authority.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%2C%20which%20has%20been%20frequently%20criticised%20by%20the%20US%20for%20the%20opacity%20of%20its%20nuclear%20build-up%2C%20scrapped%20nuclear%20talks%20with%20Washington%20in%20July%20over%20U.S.%20arms%20sales%20to%20Taiwan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20has%20more%20than%20500%20operational%20nuclear%20warheads%20in%20its%20arsenal%2C%20of%20which%20approximately%20350%20are%20ICBMs%2C%20and%20will%20probably%20have%20over%201%2C000%20warheads%20by%202030%2C%20the%20Pentagon%20estimated%20last%20year.%20China's%20milit